<Layout title="Hero & Squad Meta" description="Which Last War: Survival heroes to invest in, squad composition rules, wishlist strategy, and when to start a second squad.">
  <h1>Hero &amp; Squad Meta</h1>
  <p class="text-lg text-[#8a96b0]">Who gets your shards, how to build the squad around them, and when squad #2 starts. Last verified: July 2026.</p>

  <QuickSummary>
    <p><strong>Build exactly one squad of 5 before anything else gets a single shard.</strong> Tank meta first (Kimberly carry), mono-type always, race carry + tank to 5★ (it gates EW and Wall of Honor). A 5★ SSR beats a 1–2★ UR — don't bench proven power for potential.</p>
  </QuickSummary>

  <h2>Squad Composition Rules</h2>
  <ul class="text-sm space-y-1">
    <li><strong>Mono-type is non-negotiable:</strong> 5 same-type heroes = +20% ATK/DEF/HP to the whole march (3 = +5%, 3+2 = +10%, 4 = +15%). A mono squad of weaker heroes usually beats a mixed squad of stronger ones.</li>
    <li><strong>2 front / 3 back:</strong> tanks with Damage Reduction up front; skill DPS and support behind. Never put DPS in front.</li>
    <li><strong>The one sanctioned exception</strong> is the "Murphy Exception" 4+1 hybrid — his personal tankiness (with his EW at 20+) can outweigh the lost 5% formation bonus, mainly in Aircraft squads. The Marshall 4+1 variant is the other debated hybrid; pure mono remains the safe default.</li>
    <li><strong>Type counters</strong> (Tank &gt; Missile &gt; Aircraft &gt; Tank, ±20% both ways) decide close fights; a large raw-power lead overrides them.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Who to Invest In (2026 Consensus)</h2>
  <div class="table-wrapper">
    <table>
      <caption class="sr-only">Key heroes by role with investment guidance</caption>
      <thead>
        <tr><th scope="col">Role</th><th scope="col">Heroes</th><th scope="col">Notes</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><th scope="row">Tank-meta carry</th><td><strong>Kimberly</strong></td><td>The premier investment: first EW to 20, first Legendary/Mythic Gun, first Wall of Honor focus.</td></tr>
        <tr><th scope="row">Tanks (front row, Tank-type)</th><td><strong>Murphy</strong> (shield), <strong>Williams</strong> (damage reduction)</td><td>Murphy's Radar is the sanctioned Mythic detour (team-wide DR). Williams stacks DR to tank far above his power.</td></tr>
        <tr><th scope="row">Tanks (front row, own-type squads)</th><td>Lucius (Aircraft), Adam (Missile)</td><td>Lucius and Adam are Aircraft- and Missile-type heroes respectively, not Tank-type — they fill the front-line tank <em>role</em> inside their own mono-type squads, not a Tank mono squad.</td></tr>
        <tr><th scope="row">DPS / all-rounders (back row)</th><td><strong>DVA</strong> (crit burst), <strong>Tesla</strong> (hits back row directly), Fiona, Schuyler, Morrison (enemy DEF shred), Stetmann</td><td>Season EWs: S1 Kimberly/DVA/Tesla, S2 Murphy/Carlie/Swift, S3 Marshall/Schuyler/McGregor, S4 Lucius/Adam/Williams, S5 Fiona/Stetmann/Morrison. Morrison's shred stacks 5% per hit to a 25% cap over ~9s (per allclash; single-source) — it's not an instant flat −25%.</td></tr>
        <tr><th scope="row">Support</th><td><strong>Marshall</strong> (only UR support — squad crit buffs)</td><td>Marshall fits any squad type; that's what makes the 4+1 debate real. Stetmann is primarily a damage dealer/all-rounder, not a support pick, despite older tier lists grouping him here.</td></tr>
        <tr><th scope="row">Promotable SSRs</th><td><strong>Mason, Violet, Scarlett</strong></td><td>Safe investments: shards and skill medals are <em>refunded on UR promotion</em>. Mason is the Tank-meta pick; Alliance Store sells his shards.</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>
  <p class="text-sm text-[#8a96b0] mt-2">Tier lists shift each season — treat any specific ranking as a snapshot. What doesn't shift: concentrate on 5 heroes, and prefer heroes whose EWs you can actually unlock (Black Market shard boxes, Campaign Store universal fragments).</p>
  <p class="text-sm text-[#8a96b0] mt-2">The S1–S5 exclusive-weapon list above is verified, but the game has since moved into Season 6, which introduced the Hero Awakening system in place of a new EW trio. Per cpt-hedge's Season 6 guide, Hero Awakening is the current top-priority progression system — we haven't yet independently verified that prioritization or Hero Awakening's mechanics in depth, so see sources below for what's published so far.</p>

  <h2>Stars Before Everything</h2>
  <ul class="text-sm space-y-1">
    <li><strong>5★ is the hard gate</strong> for both Exclusive Weapon unlock and Wall of Honor — racing your carry and main tank to 5★ is the mid-game objective.</li>
    <li>Stars &gt; levels &gt; skills in ROI. Levels are cheap and ride HQ progression; skill medal costs spike past level 20.</li>
    <li><strong>Wishlist/Tavern:</strong> set your Wish Hero to your carry — ~10 shards of your chosen hero per 200 recruits. Change it only when the carry caps.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>When Does Squad #2 Start?</h2>
  <ul class="text-sm space-y-1">
    <li>Only after squad #1 is all 5★ with its carry EW at 20 — and even then, squad #2 gets hand-me-down gear only.</li>
    <li><strong>The Aircraft transition</strong> (~server day 70+ claim) is genuinely contested: some servers' metas demand it, others stay Tank-heavy. Watch what wins fights on <em>your</em> server before committing shards. Running two Tank squads mid-game is a legitimate, common path.</li>
    <li>Second squads exist for rallies, garrisons, and event marches — they can be much weaker than squad #1 and still do their job.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>SSR → UR Transition</h2>
  <ul class="text-sm space-y-1">
    <li>Keep high-star SSRs in the squad until the UR replacement has comparable investment — a 5★ SSR outperforms a 1–2★ UR.</li>
    <li>Promotable SSRs (Mason, Violet, Scarlett) are the exception to "UR only" advice: invest freely, the shards come back on promotion.</li>
  </ul>

  <p class="mt-4 text-xs text-[#8a96b0]">Sources: allclash.com tier coverage and Morrison build guide, lastwarvault.com squad building, cpt-hedge.com EW season list and Season 6/Hero Awakening guides, lastwar.wiki hero pages (Lucius, Adam), theriagames.com and heaven-guardian.com Stetmann guides, lastwar-tutorial.com hero leveling, packsify.com squad guide (2025–2026). Most figures here are corroborated across 2+ of these sources; single-sourced claims are attributed inline to their source rather than presented as settled fact. Contested calls (Aircraft transition timing, 4+1 hybrids) are labeled as contested rather than settled.</p>
</Layout>
